<HEAD>SERMON XIII.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub">On TRANQUILLITY OF MIND.</HEAD>
<EPIGRAPH>
<BIBL>P&s;ALM xv. 5.</BIBL>
<Q>&mdash;He that doth the&s;e things &s;hall never be
moved.</Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<P>TRANQUILLITY of mind,<NOTE PLACE="marg">SERM. XIII.</NOTE> or, in the
words of the text, a mind <HI>not
moved</HI> or di&s;quieted by the accidents of
life, is undoubtedly one of the greate&s;t
ble&s;&s;ings that we can po&s;&s;e&s;s on earth.
It is here mentioned as the reward of the
