now proceed. Let me then advi&s;e you,</P>
<P>In the <HI>third</HI> place, to attend to the cul|ture
and improvement of your minds.
A fund of u&s;eful knowledge, and a &s;tock
of ideas, afford much advantage for the
<PB N="280" REF="289">
enjoyment of tranquillity. I do not mean,
