contrary, when the human mind is cut off
from tho&s;e employments for which it was
de&s;igned by nature and Providence, it
preys on it&s;elf, and engenders its own mi|&s;ery.
Tranquillity is always mo&s;t likely
to be attained, when the bu&s;ine&s;s of the
