and devotion, a good man enjoys
him&s;elf in peace. He beholds nobler ob|jects
<PB N="290" REF="299">
than what worldly men can b$ hold.
He a&s;&s;umes a higher character. He $$|tens
to the voice of nature and of God;
and from this holy &s;anctuary comes forth
