&s;leeps in the grave; is to tran&s;mit your|&s;elves
to tho&s;e who &s;hall &s;ucceed you, as
unfeeling and ba&s;e. <HI>Thine own friend,
and they father's friend, for&s;ake not.</HI></P>
<P>I HAVE pointed out &s;ome of the chief
duties which belong to virtuous friend|&s;hip;
and &s;ome of the principal means
