unbroken; this holy flame &s;hould
be kept alive in the human brea&s;t. the
&s;pirit, and &s;entiments, which I have &s;tu|died
to in&s;pire are &s;uch as virtue breathes,
and &s;uch as true piety &s;hould increa&s;e.
it is thus we fulfil that great law of love,
which our divine Ma&s;ter taught. It is
thus we prepare our&s;elves for tho&s;e happy
