as &s;oon as they contradicted the reigning
cu&s;toms and fa&s;hions of the world.&mdash;
While &s;uch conduct carries in it &s;o much
wickedne&s;s and folly, let us ob&s;erve,</P>
<P>IN the <HI>fourth</HI> place, that mo&s;t excel|lent
and honourable character which can a|dorn
<PB N="415" REF="424">
a man and a chri&s;tian, is acquired,
